1
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,519
Professor Fan

2
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:02,980
Ms. Liu

3
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:04,319
Thanks, kid

4
00:02:05,939 --> 00:02:07,239
Ms. Liu, please sit

5
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,259
Thank you

6
00:02:09,939 --> 00:02:10,939
This is for my...

7
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,060
...published collection...

8
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:14,139
...a small celebration ceremony

9
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:16,280
Thank you

10
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:18,439
Just...

11
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,620
...the two of us?

12
00:02:19,699 --> 00:02:20,699
Just two people?

13
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:21,699
Isn't that nice?

14
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:26,840
I mean, aren't you afraid...

15
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,639
...of gossip spreading in our community?

16
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:29,759
So what?

17
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:34,159
No, I was thinking, if...

18
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:35,360
...we invited one more person...

19
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,599
...it would be nice to be together

20
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:38,960
I don't think that's necessary

21
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,319
I'm treating you, Ms. Liu, to dinner

22
00:02:41,419 --> 00:02:42,099
What's wrong with that?

23
00:02:42,639 --> 00:02:44,680
Why fear gossip in the community?

24
00:02:44,819 --> 00:02:47,159
I'm mainly worried about Boss Li

25
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,120
If he knew...

26
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,120
...that the two of us were eating alone together...

27
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,479
...he probably wouldn't be happy

28
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,719
He would inevitably...

29
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,319
...gossip about this and that

30
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,000
I don't care about any Boss Li

31
00:02:56,539 --> 00:02:58,000
If he hears about it and gets unhappy...

32
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,439
...it has nothing to do with me

33
00:02:59,659 --> 00:03:00,699
That's his own problem

34
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:01,840
How could that be?

35
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:04,199
If Old Li heard... Boss Li...

36
00:03:04,259 --> 00:03:05,699
...would also be very happy

37
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:07,180
Ms. Liu, please sit

38
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:08,039
Okay, thanks

39
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:08,719
Professor Fan

40
00:03:09,219 --> 00:03:09,919
You sit too

41
00:03:10,099 --> 00:03:10,759
Don't stand on ceremony

42
00:03:10,939 --> 00:03:12,319
Your nose is quite sharp

43
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:15,340
A single nose...

44
00:03:15,659 --> 00:03:16,939
...how much power can it have?

45
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:19,800
Organs must help each other...

46
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:22,479
...to see all directions and hear all quarters

47
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,060
Only then can the tongue taste a hundred flavors...

48
00:03:24,139 --> 00:03:25,280
...and enjoy spicy and savory food

49
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:26,199
That is...

50
00:03:26,199 --> 00:03:27,479
...coming uninvited...

51
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:29,139
...face thick as a city wall

52
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,719
...mooching food and drink...

53
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:32,120
...bowls clean and plates empty

54
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:33,360
...eating and taking...

55
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,680
...either stealing or robbing

56
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,520
Alright, Professor Fan

57
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:37,060
Say a little less

58
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:39,099
It's just adding a pair of chopsticks

59
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:41,520
How can one pair of chopsticks be enough?

60
00:03:41,879 --> 00:03:44,120
As a roommate sharing a room with Professor Fan...

61
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,439
...eating, living, and working together...

62
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:48,139
I have an obligation...

63
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,860
...to help him improve relations with the masses

64
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,099
So I invited a host of heroes...

65
00:03:53,180 --> 00:03:55,000
...and sent out hero invitations everywhere

66
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:57,360
Come on, children

67
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:58,500
Come on

68
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,900
Coming

69
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:00,819
Hello, elders

70
00:04:00,819 --> 00:04:03,800
Grandma Liu, Grandpa Fan

71
00:04:05,259 --> 00:04:06,259
Sit

72
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:07,280
Don't be shy, everyone

73
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:07,620
Sit

74
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,060
You sit over there

75
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:08,479
You're welcome

76
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:10,159
Everyone coming gives me face

77
00:04:10,259 --> 00:04:11,460
Today, everyone...

78
00:04:11,479 --> 00:04:13,439
...must order their favorite dish

79
00:04:13,939 --> 00:04:14,180
Okay

80
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:14,659
Boss Li

81
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:16,040
Are you treating?

82
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:16,480
Yes

83
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,319
I'm treating

84
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,240
Professor Fan pays the bill

85
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,839
After all...

86
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,959
...I haven't received my royalties...

87
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,720
...how can I afford to treat?

88
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,279
As...

89
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:26,420
...Old Fan's roommate who eats, lives, and works with him...

90
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,399
...I need to organize things for him

91
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:30,879
So,

92
00:04:31,019 --> 00:04:32,040
can we order now?

93
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,720
Order away.

94
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,060
Let's get a meat dish.

95
00:04:34,620 --> 00:04:35,420
Dongpo pork elbow.

96
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:36,980
Grandpa Li,

97
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,639
the food at our retirement community

98
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:40,300
is just way too healthy.

99
00:04:40,339 --> 00:04:41,560
I'm starved for meat.

100
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,360
Order it!

101
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:43,459
Add a fish, too.

102
00:04:43,459 --> 00:04:44,279
Two fish.

103
00:04:44,279 --> 00:04:44,879
Two.

104
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,720
Since we're having fish,

105
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,639
let's get shrimp. Braised prawns.

106
00:04:47,639 --> 00:04:48,220
That's the one.

107
00:04:48,259 --> 00:04:50,180
Can we order one to go?

108
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:50,879
Sure.

109
00:04:50,980 --> 00:04:52,959
Wang Song is on duty today.

110
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,800
Is that really for Wang Song?

111
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:57,199
You'll just eat it as a midnight snack.

112
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:57,720
So what?

113
00:04:57,759 --> 00:04:59,259
You never miss a midnight snack.

114
00:04:59,339 --> 00:05:00,899
You just rely on eating without getting fat.

115
00:05:00,939 --> 00:05:01,579
I don't gain weight.

116
00:05:01,579 --> 00:05:02,439
I just don't gain weight.

117
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,379
Unlike you.

118
00:05:03,379 --> 00:05:04,220
You've got plenty of meat on you.

119
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:04,980
You definitely gain weight.

120
00:05:05,019 --> 00:05:06,019
Get him a roast duck.

121
00:05:06,019 --> 00:05:06,660
To go.

122
00:05:06,819 --> 00:05:07,240
Okay.

123
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:11,699
Auntie Cai.

124
00:05:12,379 --> 00:05:13,000
Hello there.

125
00:05:13,699 --> 00:05:14,860
Director Chang is here.

126
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:16,399
Who's this young man?

127
00:05:16,459 --> 00:05:17,459
Let me introduce you.

128
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,920
This is Xiao Long.

129
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,480
He's the community's newly hired...

130
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,360
massage therapist.

131
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,800
He specializes in serving seniors.

132
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,939
Hello, Auntie Cai.

133
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,420
That's great.

134
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:28,800
He's quite a handsome boy.

135
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,079
How old are you?

136
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,480
Are you married?

137
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:35,939
Is everyone done?

138
00:05:37,259 --> 00:05:38,360
No need to add more dishes?

139
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,180
We could add a couple.

140
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:41,800
Zhu Zhu.

141
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,120
That's enough.

142
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:43,759
Look,

143
00:05:44,379 --> 00:05:46,040
the plates are licked clean.

144
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,000
We didn't leave anything for Wang Song.

145
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,079
Xiaoxin, bill please.

146
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,899
That's 720 in total.

147
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,100
Just give me 700.

148
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:54,959
Don't.

149
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,019
Let's stick to 720.

150
00:05:56,019 --> 00:05:56,500
It's easier to calculate.

151
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:58,839
There are seven of us.

152
00:05:58,839 --> 00:05:59,839
Ninety per person.

153
00:06:00,079 --> 00:06:01,139
Zhu Zhu, you pay double.

154
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,720
Why should I?

155
00:06:03,019 --> 00:06:04,360
You ate more than your share.

156
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:06,199
I saw you eat enough for three people just now.

157
00:06:07,459 --> 00:06:08,139
What does that mean?

158
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:09,459
What's going on here?

159
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,500
Splitting the bill.

160
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:11,579
Everyone pays for themselves.

161
00:06:11,579 --> 00:06:12,399
It's the old rule.

162
00:06:12,459 --> 00:06:13,259
That's a good rule.

163
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:14,680
I'm all for it.

164
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,439
I'll pay for you.

165
00:06:15,439 --> 00:06:15,899
No.

166
00:06:15,899 --> 00:06:16,819
No need.

167
00:06:16,819 --> 00:06:17,699
No need, Professor Fan.

168
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,259
I know how to use WeChat Pay.

169
00:06:19,259 --> 00:06:20,560
Ms. Liu knows how.

170
00:06:20,939 --> 00:06:21,860
Besides,

171
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:22,680
if we're splitting,

172
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:24,420
I should be the one covering Ms. Liu.

173
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:25,720
Wait, that's not right.

174
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,480
Today is your treat.

175
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,379
I didn't invite you.

176
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,759
Am I that passive?

177
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:33,000
To wait for someone to offer to treat me?

178
00:06:33,139 --> 00:06:34,639
You need to read the room.

179
00:06:35,339 --> 00:06:36,959
Didn't you get your royalties?

180
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,879
That's why we're all gathered here.

181
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,000
It's not right to welch on this.

182
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,240
Who's trying to welch?

183
00:06:42,379 --> 00:06:43,259
Professor Fan,

184
00:06:43,339 --> 00:06:45,220
we appreciate the gesture.

185
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,980
But the old rule stands.

186
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:49,300
Old rules are meant to be broken.

187
00:06:49,459 --> 00:06:50,579
No construction without destruction.

188
00:06:50,819 --> 00:06:51,500
Fine.

189
00:06:51,699 --> 00:06:52,540
Boss Li, how about this.

190
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,439
Next time you treat,

191
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:55,800
we'll break the rule then.

192
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:56,740
How does that sound?

193
00:06:56,899 --> 00:06:57,480
That works too.

194
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:58,959
Why should I?

195
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,819
I didn't get any royalties.

196
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,139
It's not like I can't get them.

197
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,420
If we break it,

198
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:05,860
we have to break it this time.

199
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:06,779
This time

200
00:07:06,839 --> 00:07:09,259
is the best time to break old habits.

201
00:07:09,259 --> 00:07:09,819
Boss Li,

202
00:07:10,139 --> 00:07:12,199
Splitting the bill isn't an old habit.

203
00:07:12,259 --> 00:07:14,480
It's an advanced practice from abroad.

204
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,439
We should take the lead in promoting it.

205
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:18,040
We take the lead in promoting it.

206
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,040
Kid,

207
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:20,420
swallow what's in your mouth

208
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:21,459
before you speak.

209
00:07:21,519 --> 00:07:22,560
Or you'll choke.

210
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,220
It's fine.

211
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:26,620
Is foreign experience necessarily advanced?

212
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,120
I don't think so.

213
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,180
Whoever invites,

214
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:31,040
pays the bill.

215
00:07:31,339 --> 00:07:31,939
This is part of our

216
00:07:31,939 --> 00:07:34,779
traditional Chinese dining culture.

217
00:07:34,839 --> 00:07:36,259
And it has a long history.

218
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,899
A long history

219
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,360
doesn't necessarily mean correct.

220
00:07:39,540 --> 00:07:40,939
Foot binding and opium smoking

221
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,079
also had long histories.

222
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:43,399
China is developing.

223
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:44,360
The country is progressing.

224
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,839
Only a blockhead

225
00:07:46,060 --> 00:07:47,060
would refuse to accept change.

226
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:47,959
Who?

227
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,040
A blockhead?

228
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,839
You two,

229
00:07:50,839 --> 00:07:53,220
can you stop bickering for a moment?

230
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,740
Not in front of the kids.

231
00:07:54,839 --> 00:07:56,579
We were born in the reform era.

232
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,439
We're more open to new things.

233
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:00,399
Older people

234
00:08:00,459 --> 00:08:01,420
sticking to tradition

235
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,740
is understandable too.

236
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:03,980
Let me think.

237
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,720
Which is actually better?

238
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:08,339
Accepting the new?

239
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:10,100
Or sticking to tradition?

240
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,519
Ms. Liu

241
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,160
Which one do you think is better?

242
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:15,819
I'll stand on whichever side you're on.

243
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,160
I...

244
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,519
I haven't quite wrapped my head around it yet.

245
00:08:19,579 --> 00:08:20,519
I'm the same as you.

246
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,660
I haven't wrapped my head around it either.

247
00:08:21,759 --> 00:08:24,019
Anyway, I firmly support splitting the bill.

248
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,540
Whatever you support, I oppose.

249
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:27,300
I support splitting the bill for meals.

250
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,699
It shows I have a youthful mindset.

251
00:08:28,740 --> 00:08:30,120
It doesn't show you have a youthful mindset.

252
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,300
It only shows you're stingy.

253
00:08:31,819 --> 00:08:33,299
It shows your old brain isn't open to new things.

254
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,019
You're an old cucumber painted green.

255
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:35,980
You're painting it even thicker.

256
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,960
Alright, can you two stop bickering?

257
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,259
It's okay, Grandma Liu.

258
00:08:40,259 --> 00:08:40,679
I...

259
00:08:40,779 --> 00:08:41,840
just love watching them fight.

260
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:43,779
Fine.

261
00:08:44,059 --> 00:08:45,440
For the sake of Ms. Liu...

262
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,799
I'll let you off the hook today.

263
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,659
But I must tell you...

264
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:49,539
children...

265
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,200
although we are older than you...

266
00:08:53,379 --> 00:08:54,220
by a year or two...

267
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,960
if we start playing...

268
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,860
we play at a higher level than you.

269
00:08:57,259 --> 00:08:58,600
You guys care about splitting the bill.

270
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:58,980
Right.

271
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,460
If we play, it's taking turns treating.

272
00:09:01,659 --> 00:09:02,580
Today he treats.

273
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:03,980
Tomorrow I treat.

274
00:09:04,159 --> 00:09:04,799
The day after tomorrow...

275
00:09:05,659 --> 00:09:06,320
he treats again.

276
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,879
Why is it me again?

277
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,100
It should be...

278
00:09:09,259 --> 00:09:09,840
your turn.

279
00:09:10,039 --> 00:09:10,960
Why should it be me?

280
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:11,940
Of course it's you.

281
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:12,620
I have to say,

282
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,580
Grandpa Boss Li is an upgraded version.

283
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:15,960
AA 2.0.

284
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,019
Still eating?

285
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:18,620
Let's go, Ms. Liu.

286
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,440
Are you okay?

287
00:09:33,659 --> 00:09:34,320
I'm fine.

288
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:35,779
It's just a little itchy.

289
00:09:35,779 --> 00:09:36,139
It's fine.

290
00:09:36,139 --> 00:09:36,820
You carry on.

291
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:47,539
Me?

292
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:49,139
I'm ticklish all over

293
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,100
I can't be touched

294
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,620
What should I do then?

295
00:09:52,919 --> 00:09:54,120
It's fine

296
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,720
Go over to Number 3

297
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,440
try Uncle Liang

298
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,580
He loves that stuff

299
00:09:58,679 --> 00:09:59,700
Okay, Auntie Cai

300
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:00,539
I'll go right now

301
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,399
Hey

302
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:02,820
Xiao Long

303
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:03,840
Do you really

304
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:05,000
not have a girlfriend?

305
00:10:05,259 --> 00:10:05,919
Well...

306
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:07,419
how should I put it?

307
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:08,820
Just tell the truth

308
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:10,279
Either you do or you don't

309
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,980
Back in my hometown

310
00:10:12,259 --> 00:10:13,600
my parents introduced one

311
00:10:14,340 --> 00:10:15,340
But I didn't like her

312
00:10:15,759 --> 00:10:16,840
There was no love

313
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:20,399
Arranged marriage? No way

314
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:21,500
It's a lifelong commitment

315
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:23,100
How can it work without love?

316
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,179
Come here

317
00:10:25,139 --> 00:10:25,899
Don't worry

318
00:10:25,899 --> 00:10:26,480
It's no problem

319
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:28,899
Auntie Cai will introduce one to you

320
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:30,360
Young and beautiful

321
00:10:30,399 --> 00:10:31,740
with a great personality

322
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:34,179
I guarantee the moment you meet

323
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:36,039
love will strike immediately

324
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,139
What's the harm in meeting?

325
00:10:39,299 --> 00:10:40,360
That young man

326
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,340
has great prospects

327
00:10:42,659 --> 00:10:44,299
Tall and handsome

328
00:10:44,419 --> 00:10:45,740
He'd make a great boyfriend

329
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:47,919
He has skills

330
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,980
and a good personality too

331
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:51,399
Let me put it this way

332
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:53,879
his biggest flaw is

333
00:10:54,059 --> 00:10:55,179
he's too outstanding

334
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:57,799
How is being outstanding a flaw?

335
00:10:58,159 --> 00:10:59,559
Being too outstanding...

336
00:10:59,779 --> 00:11:00,299
think about it

337
00:11:00,340 --> 00:11:01,200
In your lifetime

338
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:03,399
how many girls will compete with you?

339
00:11:03,399 --> 00:11:04,039
Isn't that annoying?

340
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:04,960
Isn't that a flaw?

341
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,980
If he's really as great as you say

342
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,720
how come he doesn't have a girlfriend?

343
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:10,559
Back in our village

344
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:12,259
if someone isn't married by now

345
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:13,799
there's definitely something wrong with them

346
00:11:14,419 --> 00:11:15,820
No

347
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:16,980
There's absolutely nothing wrong

348
00:11:17,559 --> 00:11:18,340
Xiao Long here

349
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:19,940
mouth isn't crooked, eyes aren't crossed

350
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,639
He doesn't limp at all, right?

351
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,320
He is totally a... what is it?

352
00:11:23,639 --> 00:11:25,019
An idol youth

353
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:25,679
Who?

354
00:11:25,759 --> 00:11:26,299
Who?

355
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,759
Who?

356
00:11:27,759 --> 00:11:30,120
Who's still attached?

357
00:11:30,259 --> 00:11:31,600
How did we wake her up?

358
00:11:33,039 --> 00:11:34,360
Go back to sleep

359
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,019
I'm not sleepy

360
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,840
The moon is bright

361
00:11:40,899 --> 00:11:42,179
The wind...

362
00:11:54,539 --> 00:11:55,240
What are you looking at?

363
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:56,899
Seeing when you're gonna treat me.

364
00:11:58,419 --> 00:11:59,100
Is that all?

365
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:00,500
You've been harping on this all afternoon.

366
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,799
Have you not eaten anything?

367
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,580
Just waiting for me to treat you?

368
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:09,600
That's the plan.

369
00:12:11,019 --> 00:12:11,480
Fine.

370
00:12:11,919 --> 00:12:13,279
You really are something.

371
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:15,220
This guy...

372
00:12:16,019 --> 00:12:16,620
Okay.

373
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,519
I'll give you a firm date.

374
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:23,379
The day I receive my writing fee

375
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:25,799
is the day you get your feast.

376
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:26,799
You promise?

377
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,620
When has Old Li ever broken his word?

378
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,460
So when do you get the fee?

379
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:30,860
Soon.

380
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:32,200
Specifically.

381
00:12:32,559 --> 00:12:34,000
Specifically when?

382
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:35,679
Well, I have to wait for the article to be published.

383
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:37,759
So when will your article be published?

384
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:38,860
Well, I have to write it first.

385
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,980
So when will you write it?

386
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,899
Once I've thought it through, I'll write it.

387
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:43,960
So when will you...

388
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:46,919
You haven't even decided what to write?

389
00:12:47,139 --> 00:12:48,620
You're spending this meal on credit?

390
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,600
Spending tomorrow's money.

391
00:12:50,299 --> 00:12:52,539
You're really getting way ahead of yourself.

392
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,000
Auntie Cai.

393
00:13:00,379 --> 00:13:01,259
Auntie Cai.

394
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:03,700
A Jian? Do you need something?

395
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,779
Shh, keep your voice down.

396
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:07,679
Do you need something?

397
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:13,139
You looking for me?

398
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,480
You can speak up now.

399
00:13:14,759 --> 00:13:15,299
What is it?

400
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,600
You'd better keep it down.

401
00:13:17,779 --> 00:13:18,399
Auntie Cai.

402
00:13:18,679 --> 00:13:19,960
I heard you're playing matchmaker.

403
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,899
Setting Xiaofang up with that new guy, Xiao Long.

404
00:13:22,179 --> 00:13:22,960
That's right.

405
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,519
You even heard about that?

406
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:26,159
What do you think?

407
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:26,919
They're a good match, right?

408
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:28,100
Are they?

409
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:29,340
If there's such a good opportunity...

410
00:13:29,340 --> 00:13:30,799
Why didn't you introduce her to me?

411
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:34,580
Right.

412
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:36,500
You're still single, aren't you?

413
00:13:37,139 --> 00:13:38,440
I overlooked that.

414
00:13:39,580 --> 00:13:41,039
Auntie will find you another one.

415
00:13:41,179 --> 00:13:41,580
Tell me.

416
00:13:41,639 --> 00:13:42,659
What kind do you want?

417
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:43,919
I don't want any kind.

418
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,059
I just like Xiaofang.

419
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,419
No problem.

420
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,320
Later I'll just...

421
00:13:48,899 --> 00:13:50,460
You like Xiaofang too?

422
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,559
Isn't that a conflict?

423
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:53,580
Just...

424
00:13:55,519 --> 00:13:56,580
Look at you, kid.

425
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:57,179
These feelings of yours...

426
00:13:57,179 --> 00:13:59,179
You didn't tell your Auntie sooner.

427
00:13:59,279 --> 00:14:00,320
How could I tell you?

428
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,200
I didn't know if...

429
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,580
Xiaofang would be willing or not.

430
00:14:02,679 --> 00:14:03,820
I can't just go blabbing everywhere.

431
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,679
Nothing's even happened yet.

432
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:07,799
You haven't even made a move yet.

433
00:14:07,879 --> 00:14:09,500
Let's not talk about that, it's not important.

434
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:10,480
The problem is...

435
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:11,700
That girl Xiaofang...

436
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,340
She can't be split in half, right?

437
00:14:13,379 --> 00:14:14,799
Splitting her into pieces wouldn't help.

438
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,559
It's all your fault.

439
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:17,639
I was proceeding according to plan.

440
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:18,759
I thought once I went permanent...

441
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:19,820
I'd confess my feelings to her.

442
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:21,539
Who knew you'd butt in like this.

443
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:23,120
You cut in, and he won the hand.

444
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,080
I just handed Xiaofang over to Xiao Long.

445
00:14:25,919 --> 00:14:26,679
Don't worry, kid.

446
00:14:26,679 --> 00:14:27,139
Don't worry.

447
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:29,299
Auntie will find you a good one later.

448
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,220
Come on, I...

449
00:14:30,559 --> 00:14:32,100
You don't want... look what you've done.

450
00:14:32,779 --> 00:14:33,519
Let's think.

451
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,299
Let's see if there's a better way.

452
00:14:36,639 --> 00:14:37,600
Competition!

453
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:38,799
Our A Jian...

454
00:14:38,799 --> 00:14:40,580
Can totally compete fairly with him.

455
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:40,940
That's right.

456
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:41,700
Exactly.

457
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:43,840
Our A Jian isn't stupid or slow.

458
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,639
What do you mean "not stupid or slow"?

459
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:47,360
He's practically capable and smart.

460
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:49,399
Simply cultivated inside and out.

461
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:51,460
Totally got both brains and brawn.

462
00:14:51,639 --> 00:14:53,639
If he doesn't join a boy band...

463
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,279
It's a total waste of talent.

464
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,299
I think...

465
00:14:56,419 --> 00:14:57,720
We should help A Jian.

466
00:14:57,779 --> 00:14:59,379
Come up with some practical ideas.

467
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,139
I actually have an idea.

468
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:02,419
I just don't know...

469
00:15:02,419 --> 00:15:03,100
If it'll work.

470
00:15:05,899 --> 00:15:06,940
Is this okay, Uncle Liang?

471
00:15:07,620 --> 00:15:09,240
Is it too hard?

472
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,240
Not at all.

473
00:15:10,399 --> 00:15:11,299
It's perfect.

474
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,299
Feels good.

475
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:14,559
If you...

476
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:15,860
Aren't afraid of getting tired...

477
00:15:15,919 --> 00:15:17,080
Use a bit more force.

478
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,059
Your Uncle Liang can take it.

479
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:18,639
Okay.

480
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:20,919
Come in.

481
00:15:27,279 --> 00:15:28,220
Uncle Liang.

482
00:15:28,539 --> 00:15:30,000
I'm here to clean for you.

483
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,340
Go ahead.

484
00:15:31,539 --> 00:15:31,860
I...

485
00:15:31,860 --> 00:15:32,919
I won't chat with you anymore.

486
00:15:32,919 --> 00:15:33,860
You go about your business.

487
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:44,580
Brother Liu speaks

488
00:15:47,460 --> 00:15:50,039
with too much bias

489
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:52,980
You young lady are from our Henan too?

490
00:15:53,379 --> 00:15:54,039
That's right.

491
00:15:54,519 --> 00:15:56,080
Which part of Henan are you from?

492
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,100
I'm from Zhumadian.

493
00:15:57,159 --> 00:15:57,740
And you?

494
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:58,600
Me?

495
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,559
I'm from Shangqiu.

496
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,019
You two have found a fellow townsman.

497
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:07,320
We're all away from home making a living.

498
00:16:07,559 --> 00:16:08,639
How many kids do you have back home?

499
00:16:08,639 --> 00:16:09,500
Just two.

500
00:16:09,799 --> 00:16:10,600
Two?

501
00:16:11,019 --> 00:16:12,580
You started a family so young?

502
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,139
We settle down early back there.

503
00:16:15,759 --> 00:16:16,580
No.

504
00:16:16,940 --> 00:16:17,799
No?

505
00:16:18,679 --> 00:16:20,299
You have two kids without being married?

506
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:21,659
No.

507
00:16:21,879 --> 00:16:22,879
I mean...

508
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,919
there is no love.

509
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,320
Easy there, you.

510
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,379
Are you done yet?

511
00:16:34,659 --> 00:16:36,220
You latch onto me for food and won't let go.

512
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,159
Courtesy demands reciprocity.

513
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,580
It's also our nation's excellent tradition.

514
00:16:40,639 --> 00:16:42,720
It is indecent not to reciprocate.

515
00:16:43,139 --> 00:16:43,840
Don't talk nonsense.

516
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:45,759
Who did I act indecently with?

517
00:16:48,259 --> 00:16:49,059
Fine.

518
00:16:50,039 --> 00:16:50,559
I'll treat.

519
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:52,039
I'll treat, okay?

520
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:53,220
Time?

521
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:54,139
Tonight.

522
00:16:54,559 --> 00:16:55,120
Location?

523
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:56,159
Private room.

524
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:58,440
I didn't say I was inviting you.

525
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:01,820
I didn't invite you yesterday,

526
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,139
but you showed up anyway.

527
00:17:03,799 --> 00:17:05,599
I need to have the sense to come today too.

528
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,019
We're roommates, after all.

529
00:17:07,519 --> 00:17:08,099
Old Li...

530
00:17:08,859 --> 00:17:09,500
took the bait.

531
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:18,859
What?

532
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:20,480
That Xiao Long...

533
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:22,039
he already has a wife.

534
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:24,059
He's been married for three years.

535
00:17:24,140 --> 00:17:25,680
He's got a wife and kids all set.

536
00:17:26,099 --> 00:17:26,880
What?

537
00:17:27,099 --> 00:17:28,500
He even has kids?

538
00:17:28,599 --> 00:17:29,420
Two of them.

539
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:30,779
Old enough to run errands.

540
00:17:31,099 --> 00:17:31,740
Kids...

541
00:17:33,359 --> 00:17:33,920
Wait,

542
00:17:34,279 --> 00:17:36,319
didn't he say there was no love?

543
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,039
That doesn't stop him from having kids.

544
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:41,119
What kind of person is he?

545
00:17:41,119 --> 00:17:42,019
I need to go have a word with him.

546
00:17:42,460 --> 00:17:43,339
Auntie Cai.

547
00:17:43,519 --> 00:17:44,759
What is there to say?

548
00:17:44,839 --> 00:17:46,799
It's not illegal to get married and have kids.

549
00:17:46,859 --> 00:17:47,460
True.

550
00:17:47,519 --> 00:17:49,940
We marry and have kids early back there.

551
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:50,680
Yes.

552
00:17:50,799 --> 00:17:52,980
But you shouldn't hide it, right?

553
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:54,920
Making me do all this work for nothing.

554
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:56,380
In front of that Xiaofang,

555
00:17:56,380 --> 00:17:58,279
I praised him to the skies.

556
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:00,660
Then let's pull back from the brink.

557
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:01,700
Better late than never.

558
00:18:01,759 --> 00:18:04,019
Just switch to praising A Jian to the skies.

559
00:18:04,079 --> 00:18:05,200
Won't that work?

560
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,200
Alright.

561
00:18:06,559 --> 00:18:07,240
I'll go right now.

562
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:08,500
Wait, I can't go yet.

563
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:10,519
Boss Li is hosting a feast.

564
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,900
Professor Fan said I must go.

565
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,299
He's so annoying.

566
00:18:14,299 --> 00:18:15,420
Treating me to dinner again.

567
00:18:18,380 --> 00:18:19,799
Auntie Cai, take me with you.

568
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:32,900
Thank you, Boss Li

569
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:33,880
Thanks

570
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:34,539
Congratulations

571
00:18:34,539 --> 00:18:36,559
Congratulations to Boss Li on the writing fee

572
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,599
Fine, Old Fan. You're ruthless

573
00:18:39,059 --> 00:18:40,039
It is indeed worth celebrating

574
00:18:40,940 --> 00:18:42,039
Thanks

575
00:18:42,140 --> 00:18:42,980
The joy is mutual

576
00:18:45,779 --> 00:18:46,259
Let's order

577
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,440
Don't you worry about that

578
00:18:48,779 --> 00:18:50,900
Professor Fan has already ordered everything

579
00:18:53,039 --> 00:18:53,859
It's all ordered

580
00:18:54,359 --> 00:18:54,980
Good that it's ordered

581
00:18:56,599 --> 00:18:57,779
What exactly did you order?

582
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:58,720
A mix of meat and vegetables

583
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,900
We agreed to treat Ms. Liu

